Scope[edit]

Women's cricket aims to:

  • follow those guidelines set down by Wikipedia:WikiProject Cricket
  • increase the number of well-written cricket-related articles by expanding all stubs to start-class and improving all start-class articles to B-class at least
  • expand the biographies of everyone who has played major women's cricket with distinction; this includes all cricketers who were famous before Women's Test cricket began and all cricketers who have played in at least one Women's Test match or at least one Women's One Day International.

Participants[edit]

  1. Harrias (talk · contribs) – Currently working on creating and expanding articles relating to South African women's cricket
  2. SpacemanSpiff (talk · contribs) – Completed stubs for all India women cricketers; moving on to first class players from India
  3. Jhall1 (talk · contribs) – Will contribute as and when time permits, which may not be very often
  4. AMBerry (talk · contribs) – Slowly making the international lists, will concentrate on the Irish women to start with as well.
  5. Lavalavike (talk · contribs) – I will create a stub pages for all women cricketers who represented Karnataka Women domestic team.
  6. Ninney (talk · contribs) – My great ways to contribute would be by making minor edits/corrections to articles (e.g., typos, fixing links, adding references to new secondary sources)
  7. Nazcheema (talk · contribs) – already being involved with Bangladeshi women's cricket, it is sensible to be joining here
  8. Bahnfrend (talk · contribs) – Women's Big Bash League, including seasons, teams, players and photographs

Article alerts[edit]

Good article nominees

  • 23 Aug 2018 – Ashleigh Barty (talk · edit · hist) was GA nominated by Sportsfan77777 (t · c); start discussion

Key biographies[edit]

  • Mithali Raj, former India captain and leading run-scorer in women's ODI cricket
  • Charlotte Edwards, former England captain and former leading run-scorer in women's ODI cricket
  • Belinda Clark, former Australia captain and chief executive of Women's Cricket Australia
  • Karen Rolton, former Australia captain
  • Claire Taylor, prolific run-scorer for England
  • Debbie Hockley, New Zealand's leading run-scorer in ODIs
  • Stafanie Taylor, West Indies captain and their leading run-scorer
  • Jhulan Goswami, former India captain and leading wicket-taker in women's ODI cricket
  • Cathryn Fitzpatrick, former leading wicket-taker in ODIs
  • Rachael Heyhoe-Flint, prominent England batsman and integral in foundation of the Women's World Cup
  • Myrtle Maclagan, prominent early England batsman
  • Betty Wilson, prominent early Australia batsman
  • Enid Bakewell, prominent England all-rounder
  • Mary Duggan, prominent England bowler
  • Diana Edulji, prominent India bowler

To-do[edit]

To-do items for members of Women's cricket task force[edit]

  • Tag related articles with |Women's cricket=true
  • Find editors who have shown interest in this subject and ask them to take a look here.
  • Identify articles for creation
  • Identify articles for improvement
  • Review importance and quality of existing articles

To-do items for anyone[edit]

International cricket
  • Create articles for all red-link international cricketers: Wikipedia:WikiProject Women in Red/Sports/Cricketers
  • Create and populate Lists for all women's international teams:

Guidelines[edit]

Tagging and assessment[edit]

Any articles that are within the scope of this project should be tagged with the project banners of WikiProject Cricket (with the parameter |Women's cricket=true), and where it is a biography, WikiProject Biography. You may also find {{WikiProjectBanners}} useful.
